{{Orphan|date=July 2011}}

A '''storepedo''', or alternately '''storpedo''', is a cylindrical storage container with an attached [[parachute]]. They were used to air-drop supplies to troops and civilians from [[bomber]] aircraft during [[World War II]].

[[Category:World War II]]


{{WWII-stub}}

'''''Meldungen aus Norwegen''''' (Reports from Norway) is a series of reports on the situation in [[Occupation of Norway by Nazi Germany|occupied Norway]] during [[World War II]], by the [[Oslo]] department of the German [[Sicherheitspolizei]] (Sipo) and [[Sicherheitsdienst]] (SD). The reports were edited by Georg Wolff and distributed to German military leaders in Norway and Germany. They were typically structured with a section on the general situation ({{lang-de|Allgemeine Lage}}), a section on the resistance movement ({{lang-de|Gegner}}), and other details ({{lang-de|Lebensgebiete}}).<ref name=kl>{{cite encyclopedia |first=Stein Ugelvik |last=Larsen  | encyclopedia=[[Norsk krigsleksikon 1940-45]] |title=Meldungen aus Norwegen |language=Norwegian |editor=[[Hans Fredrik Dahl|Dahl]] |editor2=[[Guri Hjeltnes|Hjeltnes]] |editor3=[[Berit Nøkleby|Nøkleby]] |editor4=[[Nils Johan Ringdal|Ringdal]] |editor5=[[Øystein Sørensen|Sørensen]] |url= |accessdate= |year=1995 |publisher=Cappelen |location=Oslo |isbn=82-02-14138-9 |pages=266–267 }}</ref><ref name=dyrhaug>{{cite book |title=Norge okkupert! |first=Tore |last=Dyrhaug |pages=21–23 |publisher=Universitetsforlaget |language=Norwegian |location=Oslo, Bergen, Stavanger, Tromsø |year=1985 |isbn=82-00-07509-5 }}</ref>

