{{Refimprove|date=September 2015}}
'''Ball-bearing Run''' was the nickname of a war-time flight ''Stockholmsruten'' between Stockholm and  [[Leuchers]]. The flight was run by the [[Royal Norwegian Air Force]], but for political reasons operated as an ordinary [[BOAC|BOAC Flight]], aircraft having civilian registration and the Norwegian military crew wearing BOAC uniforms and British passports.<ref>''Speedbird, the complete history of BOAC'' by Robert Higham</ref>

The  Stockholmsruten was set up by the Norwegian Government, exiled in UK with the aim of transporting Norwegians having escaped from the [[German occupation of Norway|Nazi-occupied Norway]]. Several types of aircraft were used, but the backbone of Stockholmsruten was the [[Lockheed Lodestar]]

Since the aircraft also carried [[ball-bearing]]s, of greatest imporrtance to the British war industry, the flight got its nickname in UK.

